tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: All measured parameters are within normal limits except for a low HDL cholesterol (29.9 mg/dL), which is a cardiovascular risk factor. Glycemic control (HbA1c 6.3%) is at the upper end of normal, suggesting prediabetes. Renal and electrolyte parameters are normal. Recommend addressing low HDL through lifestyle modification and monitoring glycemic status.
